January 1, 1996

Seiko Epson launches magnetic venture in China+

TOKYO, Dec. 25 Kyodo

     Japanese electronics maker Seiko Epson Corp. said Monday it has
launched a joint venture in China to manufacture magnetic devices
with many applications.
     The company, based in Nagano Prefecture, central Japan, said the
new firm, Shanghai Epson Magnetics Co. (SEM), was incorporated in
Shanghai Dec. 18.
     The joint firm will manufacture and market a variety of magnetic
devices used widely in office automation, electric home appliances,
timepieces and cameras, the company said.
     The company said it especially aims to promote sales of its
high-performance and cheap rare earth bonded magnet, whose market has
expanded at an annual rate of more than 20% in recent years.



