ASIAN ECONOMIC NEWS via NewsNet
January 1, 1996

Itochu to launch joint steel venture in Thailand+

TOKYO, Dec. 26 Kyodo

     Japanese trading house Itochu Corp. said Tuesday it will launch
a joint venture in Thailand to produce and market hot-rolled steel
sheets in coil.
     The company said the venture, Siam Strip Mill Public Co., will
be jointly established in January with Siam Steel Pipe group, which
will hold a 60% stake in the new firm.
     Itochu will acquire a 10% equity while the remainder will
be owned by other partners, the company said.
     The total investment is estimated at 700 million dollars.  In
addition, the company said it will provide a loan worth 150 million
dollars to the new firm.
     The joint company will build a plant at an industrial complex
about 200 kilometers southeast of Bangkok, starting in April.
     The plant will produce 1.8 million tons of hot-rolled steel
sheets in coil annually, starting in 1998, the company said.
     Annual demand for the steel product in Thailand is estimated at
4 million tons, it said.



