ASIAN ECONOMIC NEWS via NewsNet
January 1, 1996

Toyota tops auto sales rankings in Thailand+

BANGKOK, Dec. 26 Kyodo

     Toyota Motor Corp. of Japan remained the top seller of
automobiles in Thailand during the first 11 months of this year,
Toyota Motor Thailand Co.'s data showed Tuesday.
     A total of 508,857 vehicles were sold in Thailand in the
January-November period, of which 141,771 were Toyotas, a 22.9%
increase over the 115,399 vehicles it sold there a year earlier.
     During the past 11 months, Toyota achieved a 27.9% share of the
total market, in which Japanese automakers hold a combined share of
91%, the company's data showed.
     Mercedes-Benz has been the top-ranking European car, with sales
of 13,058 vehicles, up 23.3% from a year earlier.
     Isuzu Motors Ltd. ranked second among Japanese manufacturers
with sales of 104,436 vehicles, an increase of 16.5% for a 20.5%
share of the Thai market.
     Chumphon Phorn-prapha, chairman of the Federation of Thai
Industries, said he foresees the car industry growing 8% next year,
matching the pace of Thailand's expected economic growth.



