Nippon Pillar to jointly make seals in China+

OSAKA, Dec. 28 Kyodo

     Nippon Pillar Packing Co., a manufacturer of industrial seals,
said Thursday it has set up a joint venture in China with a local
company to make seals to prevent leaks in pumps.
     The Osaka-based company has set up Shenyang Pillar Co. with
Chinese pump maker Shenyang Pump Manufactory, at a capital of 484.5
million yen, with the former holding a 49% stake and the latter a
51% stake.
     Demand is growing in China for pump seals amid the increasing
installation of petrochemical, oil refining and electricity
generating plants, said an official at Nippon Pillar Packing.



