January 1, 1996

HONG KONG: PLANS SUBMITTED TO EXTEND HK'S RAPID TRANSIT RAIL

Detailed financial and project plans for a $2.5bn extension to the
rapid transit rail system will be submitted to the Hong Kong government
by the Mass Transit Railway Corporation early in 1996. MTRC project
director, Russell Black, said proposals for the first part of the
extension, a 2km tunnel to provide an easier passenger connection
between the Kwun Tong and Island Lines will be lodged in January. Those
for the second section, involving 9km of new track and six stations
from Lam Tin, on the Kwun Tong line, to Tseung Kwan O, will be sent to
the government in March.

The reports will contain construction estimates, projected passenger
revenue and proposed completion dates. Work on both is due to start in
1998. The MTRC has recently invited consultants to prequalify for
design following the completion of the feasibility study by Maunsell
Consultants Asia.



