January 1, 1996

RANGOON PORT DEPOT JV

The Myanmar Port Authority (MPA) and Singapore's Allied Container
Services have agreed to form a company to build and operate a depot in
Rangoon port. MPA will hold a 51 per cent stake in the venture and
Allied will hold the remaining 49 per cent. The new venture, called MPA-
Allied Yangon Inland Container Depot plans to complete the first phase
of building in six months. The depot's final capacity will be 500
loaded and 3,500 empty cargo containers. Rangoon port handles virtually
all official Burmese imports and 90 per cent of its exports. General
cargo has risen 20 to 40 per cent during the last five years, and
containerised cargo has risen 70 to 80 per cent during the same period.



