January 1, 1996

CHIWAN WHARF HOLDINGS SIGNS UNDERWRITING AGREEMENT WITH CAZENOVE

Chiwan Wharf Holdings have signed an underwriting agreement with
Cazenove (Overseas) for the issue of an additional 40 million class B
shares. Shekou-based Chiwan Wharf has both A and B shares listed on the
Shenzhen bourse. It is the first mainland Chinese company to obtain
approval to make a second B share offer. The shares will be offered at
HK$2.90 (38 US cents) per share, based on an average closing price of
the company's class B equity between November 17 and November 29 this
year, discounted by about four per cent. A Chiwan official told the
China Securities Bulletin that the offer has a PE ratio of 9.6 times on
projected after-tax profits of Yn124m ($14.9m) for 1995. The company
plans to use the proceeds to construct grain warehouses, new berths and
other facilities.



