<A NAME = "44"></A>Copyright
ASIAN INFRASTRUCTURE MONTHLY via NewsNet
January 1, 1996

CHINA INTRODUCES AIRPORT TAX

In an effort to reform airport construction financing China has
introduced a standard departure tax from all its airports. Starting on
December 1, 1995, both Chinese and foreigners pay Yn90 ($11) to fly
abroad, and Yn50 for domestic flights. Although taxes previously varied
across all of China's airports this represents a big increase on
domestic flights. Beijing's Capital Airport used to charge Yn15 ($1.8)
on domestic flights. Foreigners were already paying Yn90 for
international flights, but Chinese residents were paying Yn60 ($7.2).



