FOREIGN INVESTMENT IN CHINESE AIRLINES NOW OPEN

Foreign investment in airlines in the form of joint ventures or share
equity is now open, according to Shen Yuankang, vice minister for
China's Civil Aviation Administration (CAAC). Shen said that foreign
investment cannot exceed 35 per cent of total capital, and foreign
investors cannot hold more than 25 per cent of the board voting rights.
CAAC has approved a 25 per cent stake of China's Hainan Airlines to be
held by an investment firm linked to US financier, George Soros.



