NISHIMATSU WINS AIRPORT CONTRACT

The Airport Authority has decided to award the contract for the
construction of the ground transportation centre to Nishimatsu
Construction. The contract has a total value of $225.7m. The building
will be sited next to the passenger terminal building. The work will
include structural works, the construction of railway works, roadworks,
an electrical substation, a switching station and an emergency
generator plantroom as well as other associated works such as ducting,
water supply and sewerage services and hard landscaping. The Mass
Transit Railway Corporation has signed an entrustment agreement with
the Airport Authority whereby the MTRC will reimburse the AA for the
