January 1, 1996

AVIATION FUEL SUPPLY WINS FRANCHISE TO OPERATE FUEL SUPPLY SYSTEM

Aviation Fuel Supply, a 10-member consortium has been awarded a 20-year
franchise to provide and operate the aviation fuel supply system at
Hong Kong's new airport, Chek Lap Kok. The initial investment will be
around HK$1.7bn ($220m). The system will include an aviation fuel
receiving facility from which the fuel will be pumped to the tank farm
on the airport. There will be capacity for 15 days' fuel to be stored
at the tank farm. Other features include an aviation fuel distribution
and hydrant system to aircraft parking locations. The members of the
consortium are Caltex Oil, Cathay Pacific, China National Aviation,
Sinopec, Caosc, China Resources Petroleum, Esso Hong Kong, Kuwait
Petroleum Aviation, Mobil Oil and Shell Developments.



