Bank Negara

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 6

THE Proposed basic guidelines for internal auditors at financial
institutions, which Bank Negara hopes to implement on January 1, will
cover at least six critical areas of banking, finance and insurance
operations.
  These are credit operations, treasury functions, derivatives, investment
in debt and equity and equity securities, information systems and
insurance underwriting and claims. THE Registrar of Companies will study
all issues arising from the implementation of the recent amendments to
Companies Act before considering re-amending or revoking them.
                               

