Telekom Malaysia signs deal with Ablelink

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 6

By Cheong Heng Weng

TELEKOM Malaysia Bhd will be undertaking works to provide
telecommunications infrastructure and facilities to the property
development projects of Ablelink Properties (M) Sdn Bhd and MH Lumber Sdn
Bhd.
  Telekom Malaysia signed agreements with the two developers in Kuala
Lumpur last Saturday, under which the telecommunications company will
design, plan, install and implement telecommunications systems and
services, including fibre optics, to meet the present and future needs of
the developers' projects.
  The company will be spending more than RM3.6 million over the next five
years to lay the infrastructure and facilities.
  Residents and tenants will then enjoy advanced services such as
integrated services digital network (ISDN), advanced toll-free, virtual
private network, advanced voice messaging and voice mail, tele-mail and
video conferencing.
  Telekom Malaysia's senior vice-president of major business and
government, Dr Mohd Khir Harun said at the signing that other products and
services that will come from this include telebanking, telestock, credit
card validation, call forwarding and three-party call.
                               

