BUSINESS TIMES (MALAYSIA) via NewsNet
September 30, 1996

Amalgamated Industrial Steel Bhd

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 7

AMALGAMATED Industrial Steel Bhd (AISB) has aborted its 100 per cent
proposed acquisition of Prisma Meridian Sdn Bhd, Infostas Engineering Sdn
Bhd and a three-for-five rights issue of 61.55 million new AISB shares of
RM0.50 each at an issue price of RM5.50 per share.
  This is because the directors have been informed that Teknologi Tenaga
Perlis Sdn Bhd (TTP)'s right to finance, construct, own and operate a gas-
fuelled combined cycle power station of 650MW in Perlis has been made void
as it has been awarded to Teknologi Tenaga Perlis Consortium Sdn Bhd.
  As a result, the company has decided to abort the proposed acquisition
and consequently not to raise equity finance required through the proposed
rights issue to invest in TTP.
                               

