Top 50 companies: Top 50 companies

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 6

THERE were two new counters in the list of Top 50 companies by market
capitalisation on September 27 1996 compared to that of a month ago on
August 30. Those making their debut were Multi Purpose and Malakoff,
replacing NST Bhd and Time Engineering.
  Telekom remained at the top position while Maybank took over Tenaga's
second spot, putting the latter at the third place. Telekom market
capitalisation fell to RM43.72 billion from RM43.92 billion a month ago.
Maybank's market worth went up to RM282.42 billion from RM27.09 billion,
while Tenaga market capitalisation was down to RM26.95 billion from
RM27.88 billion.
  Besides Telekom, nine other companies remained at their same positions
and they were Sime Darby, Petronas Gas, Resorts, UE(M), Genting, Rothmans
Bhd, Berjaya Sports Toto, Golden Hope and Ekran.
  Meanwhile the two debutantes, namely Multi Purpose and Malakoff made
their entries at the 40th and 50th positions respectively. Multi Purpose
market capitalisation stood at RM31.69 billion while that of Malakoff
stood at RM27.43 billion.
  The biggest mover was Innovest which jumped to the 34th place from its
previous ranking at the 46th spot a month ago.
                               

