September 30, 1996

Stocks rise as US rate jitters ease

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 13

SHARE prices rose 1.4 per cent over the week to Friday as the futures
market gained after the US federal reserve left interest rates untouched
mid-week, dealers said.
  The Stock Exchange of Hong Kong's key Hang Seng Index gained 167.03
points last week to finish at 11,759.39 on Friday.
  Average daily turnover amounted to HK$6.2 billion, down from the
previous week's HK$7.158 billion dollars.
  The market rose on blue-chip buys, up 29.77 points last Monday. It lost
75.43 points on Tuesday on rate jitters but recovered 0.5 per cent on
Wednesday and a further 32.60 points on Thursday.
  Friday saw the biggest gain of the week with the Hang Seng up 123.26
points.
                               

