BUSINESS TIMES (MALAYSIA) via NewsNet
September 30, 1996

Mart ends mixed on FOMC move

from BUSINESS TIMES, The New Straits Times Press (Malaysia) Berhad,
     30 Sep 1996, page 14

By Public Bank Treasury Division

THE market's immediate reaction was mixed as to the surprise move by the
Fed to leave rates unchanged at the September 24 FOMC meeting. The Fed's
action gave the market a clearer direction for interest rates as the
week's economic data turned out mildly weak.
  Consumer confidence for September was down to 111.8 against August's
112.0 and August's existing homes was also down 0.02 million to 4.13
million. More significant was the durable goods for August which dropped
3.1 per cent against a 1.4 per cent increase the previous month.
  With this, rates eventually eased and they are expected to stay soft
next week until the next FOMC meeting in November.
                               

