<A NAME = "13"></A>Copyright
BUSINESS VIETNAM via NewsNet
November 1, 1996

VIETNAM: Compensation set

from BUSINESS VIETNAM, November 1, 1996

Saigon's latest compensation rates of $2000 per square metre are
not yet set in stone, but the effect is the same since the formula
was handed down by the city's People's Committee.  Developers are
not supposed to pay compensation.  The Vietnamese party is supposed
to offer a clean site.  That is the theory.  The reality is
somewhat different.  To fast-track any property project, the
foreign developer usually has to compensate the residents.  It can
now figure in $2000 psm per resident in they invariable cost
over-runs that have to be paid to the Vietnamese partner.  That
doesn't necessarily mean that the resident will receive $2000.  The
Vietnamese partner could skim off up to 80% of the compensation.

Copyright 1996 Business Vietnam




<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
