VIETNAM: Metropole office space ready

from BUSINESS VIETNAM, November 1, 1996

Hanoi:

Metropole Centre offers 5,600 sqm of Grade A office space in a
prime location in the heart of Hanoi.  The centre is part of the
new Sofitel Metropole Hotel extension, and offers high quality
construction built to French standards.  The space is distributed
over four floors and tenants can take units of between 60 sqm and
517 spm.  Fit-outs began last August.

Prices range from $43-49 per sqm but vary according to size of
unit, floor level, lease term, etc.  There is an additional $6 per
sqm service charge per month, plus 10% government turnover tax.
The minimum lease term is two years.

The building includes central air conditioning, fire sprinklers and
emergency back-up power, as well as basement car parking.  Units
are handed over with fitted carpet, fully functional ceiling, power
points and telephone sockets.  The hotel extension includes a
restaurant, bas, fitness club and conference facilities.  Metropole
Centre tenants benefits from hotel club membership incentives,
discounts on food and beverages and preferential booking of
conference rooms.

Metropole Centre is being managed by Brooke Hillier Parker with a
full-time, on-site manager to assist tenants.  Their Hanoi
representative is Robin Holdswarth on telephone 826 6122.

