<A NAME = "14"></A>Copyright
CHINA BUSINESS INFORMATION NETWORK via NewsNet
September 25, 1996

China: Song Jian emphasizes on environmental protection

from CHINA BUSINESS INFORMATION NETWORK (CBnet), Sep. 25, 1996

Environmental protection is the key to sustainable development, said
State Councillor Song Jian in Beijing Tuesday.

Speaking at the fifth meeting of the China Council for International
Cooperation on Environment and Development, Song said China, as a
developing country, is always burdened with economic development and
environmental protection issues.

In order to realize the sustained, rapid and healthy development of the
national economy, China should solve both the environmental pollution
problems that have been left over from past, as well as the new
environmental problems that crop up in the process of development.

The council is a non-governmental advisory body consisting of Chinese
government officials, internationally-recognized figures, high-ranking
foreign officials, noted experts and professors. Suggestions made by
the council have been well received by the Chinese government.

Song said that people have reached a common understanding of the
importance of sustainable development, and that planning of economic
development must be done in connection with population, resources and
environment.

He said that China has made significant progress in the protection of
environment, but the country's environmental situation is still grim:
environmental pollution, especially in cities, continues to be
aggravating, and the areas suffering from ecological destruction are
expanding.

In some areas, environmental pollution and ecological damage have
obstructed the healthy development of the economy, and even pose direct
threats to people's health, he added.

Song said that at present, environmental protection should focus on
dealing with the comprehensive relationship between environment and
development, legal construction, expanding financial resources,
increasing input, using science and technology, expanding international
cooperation and implementing international conventions on environment.

