CHINA BUSINESS INFORMATION NETWORK via NewsNet
September 25, 1996

China: No 1 Department Store wins top int"l laurels

from CHINA BUSINESS INFORMATION NETWORK (CBnet), Sep. 25, 1996

Shanghai No 1 Department Store, one of the most prestigious department
stores in the city, has become the first retailer in the country to win
the ISO9002, an international award for management and service.

The International Standard Organization gives the certificate to
businesses which it considers are among the best in the world.

``As Shanghai opens its retail markets, the competition grows keener.
The advent of foreign retailers has put our traditional management and
service under challenge,'' Zhang Yinqi, general manager of the store
said at the award ceremony held recently.

``Although we are experienced in the retail sector, we are in need of
modernization. So we decided to commit ourselves to setting up a
quality management and guarantee system in line with international
standards,'' said Zhang.

Founded in October 1949, the Shanghai No 1 Department Store is one of
the leaders in the world of commerce in China. Its seven-story shopping
facility at a premier location on bustling Nanjing Road, along with a
number of branch stores in and out of the city, chalked up sales of
2.33 billion yuan ($280.7 million) and a profit of 123 million yuan
($14.8 million) in 1995. For 11 years in a row, it was the country's
busiest store in terms of sales.

For the first half of 1996, it registered sales of 1.22 billion yuan
($147 million), up 12.9 per cent over a year earlier.

The preparation for ISO9002 accreditation was initiated in December
1994 at the store. The store got all of its senior and middle-level
staff re-trained and worked out a series of quality management
regulations.

According to Zhang, customers shopping at the No 1 Department Store are
guaranteed with satisfaction. One area where the store should win good
response is its policy of offering refunds or exchanges on bought
goods.

``Rather than resting on its laurels, the No 1 Department Store will
seek further expansion and make itself a world-famous shopping
paradise.'' Zhang said.

Copyright 1996 China Business Information Network




