China: Shaanxi Province sells power station shares

from CHINA BUSINESS INFORMATION NETWORK (CBnet), Sep. 25, 1996

Northwest China's Shaanxi province yesterday sold part of its shares in
the New Shaanxi Weihe Power Station to a Hong Kong company.

The Hong Kong China Travel Service Group Company will have 51 per cent
of the shares of the thermal power station, worth 2.754 billion yuan,
for the next 20 years. When the contract expires, the Hong Kong company
will return the shares to the provincial Power Construction Investment
and Development Corporation.

This is the largest overseas-funded project in the province and also
the first of its kind in the country's power sector.

